						<div class="postbody">What the hell. Is this for real? &quot;Not a Homebrew game&quot;?<br /><br />This is exactly what we needed... not only we have to constantly fight to inform people that those SMB hacks with swastikas aren't really &quot;homebrew games&quot;, but now we also need to deal with people trying to discredit everyone else's effort by pushing some sort of &quot;Homebrew = shitty games, my product = REAL GAME&quot; distinction.<br /><br /><img src="https://i0.wp.com/collectorvision.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/CoD-Advert.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><br />Way to go &quot;Collectorvision&quot;, the same people who adapted real SG-1000 and MSX games like Star Soldier (Hudson), Elevator Action (Taito) and others without a license into Coleco carts and sold them as &quot;homebrews&quot;. I'm really surprised there has been no real backlash against them on the internet.<br /><br />Image from their page: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://collectorvision.com/shop/snes/sydney-hunter-and-the-caverns-of-death/">https://collectorvision.com/shop/snes/s ... -of-death/</a><!-- m --></div>

					
